<p><br /></p>

<h2 id="installing-gnome-terminal-">Installing GNOME terminal <a id="terminal"></a></h2>
<p>Install <code class="highlighter-rouge">gnome-terminal</code> using the app store or the command line.</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo apt-get install gnome-terminal
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><br /></p>
<h2 id="adding-the-app-icon-to-the-launcher-">Adding the app icon to the launcher <a id="icon"></a></h2>

<p>Choose your favority text editor to open <code class="highlighter-rouge">gnome-terminal.desktop</code> file and edit two lines
that start with <code class="highlighter-rouge">OnlyShowIn</code>.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>vi /usr/share/applications/gnome-terminal.desktop
</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>...
X-GNOME-SingleWindow<span class="o">=</span><span class="nb">false</span>
<span class="c">#OnlyShowIn=GNOME;Unity;</span>
...
<span class="nv">Exec</span><span class="o">=</span>gnome-terminal
<span class="c">#OnlyShowIn=Unity</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><br /></p>
<h2 id="configuring-">Configuring <a id="config"></a></h2>

<p>You can edit the configuaration either using a terminal or dconf-editor.</p>

<h3 id="using-terminal-">Using terminal <a id="config-terminal"></a></h3>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>gsettings <span class="nb">set </span>org.gnome.desktop.default-applications.terminal <span class="nb">exec </span>gnome-terminal
gsettings <span class="nb">set </span>org.gnome.desktop.default-applications.terminal exec-arg <span class="s1">''</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><br /></p>
<h3 id="using-dconf-editor-">Using dconf editor <a id="config-dconf"></a></h3>
<p>First install <code class="highlighter-rouge">dconf editior</code> and launch the program.</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get <span class="nb">install </span>dconf-editor
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Navigate to <code class="highlighter-rouge">org</code> &gt; <code class="highlighter-rouge">gnome</code> &gt; <code class="highlighter-rouge">desktop</code> &gt; <code class="highlighter-rouge">applications</code> &gt; <code class="highlighter-rouge">terminal</code>. <br />
Change the value of <code class="highlighter-rouge">exec</code> to <code class="highlighter-rouge">gnome-terminal</code> and <code class="highlighter-rouge">exec-arg</code> to blank (empty string);</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/linux/how-to/replace-terminal/dconf-terminal.png" alt="Dconf Setting" /></p>

<p><br /></p>
<h2 id="removing-pantheon-terminal-">Removing pantheon-terminal <a id="remove"></a></h2>

<p>This step is not necessary, but if you want to keep your machine clean, you can remove the old terminal:</p>
<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>apt-get purge pantheon-terminal
</code></pre></div></div>

